{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T04:15:54.696Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Outlier Handling"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the process of identifying and managing data points that deviate significantly from the rest of the dataset — outliers can distort analysis, skew statistical measures, and negatively impact model performance, especially for algorithms sensitive to extreme values, so they must be addressed carefully during preprocessing."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Are Outliers"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Definition"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Data points that significantly differ or deviate from the general distribution of the dataset."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Common causes"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Data entry errors"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (typographical mistakes)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Measurement errors"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (instrument malfunction)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Natural variation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (extreme but valid observations)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Anomalies"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (fraud, spam, rare events)\n- "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Noise"}, {"type": "text", "text": " in data collection"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Example"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Age data: [22, 24, 25, 27, 23, 150]\nOutlier: 15