xtreme value manager\" — outliers are data points that deviate significantly from the norm and can distort analysis or hurt model performance, so you can detect them using Z-score or IQR methods, then handle them by removing (if errors), capping/flooring (to reduce impact), transforming (log/box-cox to compress), using robust scaling (median-based), or keeping them (if they're valid anomalies like fraud), choosing the method based on whether outliers are errors or meaningful patterns."}]}]}}